  "title": {
    "en": "Dataclasses: Classes Without the Boilerplate",
    "ta": "Dataclasses: Boilerplate இல்லாத வகுப்புகள்"
  },
  "description": {
    "en": "Learn @dataclass to auto-generate __init__, __repr__, __eq__, and more. Master field(), frozen dataclasses, and __post_init__.",
    "ta": "@dataclass மூலம் __init__, __repr__, __eq__ தானாக உருவாக்க கற்றுக்கொள்ளுங்கள். field(), frozen dataclasses, __post_init__ தேர்ச்சி பெறுங்கள்."
  },
  "xp_reward": 65,
  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Vaathiyaar's Auto-Builder\n\nVaathiyaar presses a button and a class builds itself. \"Tired of writing `__init__`, `__repr__`, `__eq__` for every class? `@dataclass` generates them automatically! Just declare your fields and Python does the rest.\"\n\n### Regular Class vs Dataclass\n\n```python\n# Before: 15 lines of boilerplate\nclass Point:\n    def __init__(self, x, y):\n        self.x = x\n        self.y = y\n    def __repr__(self): ...\n    def __eq__(self, other): ...\n\n# After: 4 lines with @dataclass\n@dataclass\nclass Point:\n    x: float\n    y: float\n```\n\n### Dataclass Features\n\n| Feature | How |\n|---------|-----|\n| Auto `__init__` | Generated from field declarations |\n| Auto `__repr__` | Shows class name and all fields |\n| Auto `__eq__` | Compares all fields |\n| Default values | `name: str = 'unknown'` |\n| Frozen (immutable) | `@dataclass(frozen=True)` |\n| Post-init logic | `def __post_init__(self):` |\n\n> **Key Concept:** Dataclasses are perfect for \"data holder\" classes. If your class mainly stores data with minimal behavior, use `@dataclass` instead of writing everything by hand."
  },
